<div id="review_982076126" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/982076126" />
    <a title="Sheida" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2313734-sheida"><img alt="Sheida" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610186380p2/2313734.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/982076126?book_show_action=true">Jun 30, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sheida" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sheida" href="/user/show/2313734-sheida">Sheida</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title=" 9781843544500" href="/book/show/565629.Oscar_And_The_Lady_In_Pink">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer982076126" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16310600229331814914">OK, listen, I believe in god. I honestly do. But I also believe in subtlety and not shoving your book&apos;s message down everyone&apos;s throat. This felt like someone was constantly hitting me over the head shouting &quot;YOU MUST BELIEVE YOU MUST BELIEVE&quot;. It was only 75 pages but I&apos;m pretty sure the word &quot;god&quot; was used like 75 million times. I don&apos;t know, I just found it so hard to get a clear grasp of the story (which is a textbook &quot;sad story&quot;) and to feel for the characters when it seemed like I was bein</span>
  <span id="freeText16310600229331814914" style="display:none">OK, listen, I believe in god. I honestly do. But I also believe in subtlety and not shoving your book's message down everyone's throat. This felt like someone was constantly hitting me over the head shouting "YOU MUST BELIEVE YOU MUST BELIEVE". It was only 75 pages but I'm pretty sure the word "god" was used like 75 million times. I don't know, I just found it so hard to get a clear grasp of the story (which is a textbook "sad story") and to feel for the characters when it seemed like I was being ambushed and preached to by some overly-wise lady in pink.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16310600229331814914" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


