<div id="review_1761959877" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1761959877" />
    <a title="Sarine" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/52067747-sarine"><img alt="Sarine" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1474244613p2/52067747.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1761959877?book_show_action=true">Sep 18, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sarine" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sarine" href="/user/show/52067747-sarine">Sarine</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52067747-sarine?shelf=made-me-cry">made-me-cry</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/52067747-sarine?shelf=litterature">litterature</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1761959877" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15240512996044832361">Iv&apos;e read this book a very long time ago and Ive been re-reading it every year because this story always brings me so many mixed feelings. This is nothing like the fault in our stars. It&apos;s even much better.<br/>I&apos;m telling you, it&apos;s a hard book, a very very sad book and you cry all the way to the end. <br/>It&apos;s a very small book and short story but it&apos;s extremely good and very touchy. <br/>It&apos;s in french but there&apos;s a copy in english.<br/>I&apos;m always speechless at the end because loosing someone from this illness is</span>
  <span id="freeText15240512996044832361" style="display:none">Iv'e read this book a very long time ago and Ive been re-reading it every year because this story always brings me so many mixed feelings. This is nothing like the fault in our stars. It's even much better.<br />I'm telling you, it's a hard book, a very very sad book and you cry all the way to the end. <br />It's a very small book and short story but it's extremely good and very touchy. <br />It's in french but there's a copy in english.<br />I'm always speechless at the end because loosing someone from this illness is actually very hard. Some people won't understand but for the ones who does, I know the feeling. I know what it's like to lose someone from this shit, so I guess that's why I have an affinity with the characters and the story. I feel honestly every single time compelled to sweet Oscar.<br /> It's a hard subject, something that is in our daily lives and won't go away, sadly ,but this book/story is a gem. Hope you can find it and read it !<br />Love it so much. All of my stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15240512996044832361" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


