<div id="review_3300569923" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3300569923" />
    <a title="Cristi Ivan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/93976803-cristi-ivan"><img alt="Cristi Ivan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1615044221p2/93976803.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3300569923?book_show_action=true">Apr 25, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cristi Ivan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cristi Ivan" href="/user/show/93976803-cristi-ivan">Cristi Ivan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789736894824" href="/book/show/9694407-oscar-i-tanti-roz">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3300569923" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer974851382782109832">10 years-old kid, dying of cancer, starts to write letters to his imaginary friend, pushed from behind by the nurse that takes care of him. <br/><br/>Feeling like a monster for not liking this book, but for me, it felt like a romanticized version of some horrible thing – people dying of incurable diseases.<br/><br/>People usually have trouble accepting their imminent death, so it’s kind of difficult to believe a 10 years-old kid will accept his so quickly, just by discovering God in less than a week. <br/><br/>There are huge</span>
  <span id="freeText974851382782109832" style="display:none">10 years-old kid, dying of cancer, starts to write letters to his imaginary friend, pushed from behind by the nurse that takes care of him. <br /><br />Feeling like a monster for not liking this book, but for me, it felt like a romanticized version of some horrible thing – people dying of incurable diseases.<br /><br />People usually have trouble accepting their imminent death, so it’s kind of difficult to believe a 10 years-old kid will accept his so quickly, just by discovering God in less than a week. <br /><br />There are huge conflict points that are solved through some dumb two words sentence. Also, the ideas developed in the book are too mature for a kid and everything felt dumbed-down to look like it could have been thought by a kid. The kid’s writing style was too adult-like, including words that wouldn’t be so common in children.<br /><br />There are far better novels out there, treating the same subject. So, ** stars for me.</span>
  <a data-text-id="974851382782109832" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


